 MBOMBELA – Lifestyle prizes such as Apple products, television sets, Nespresso machines, weekend getaways and touring golf bags are all up for grabs at this first-of-a-kind event is aimed at creating a lifestyle event for this sport in and around the Lowveld. It takes place on Saturday July 28 at Ingwenyama Conference & Sports Resort in White River. Participating is a steal: the entry fee of R200 per player gets you two drinks, bar snacks, vouchers and a goody bag to the value of R400.  Craft gin and beer, pop-up food stalls, a lounge with a spa by VIP Barber, free dartboard golf and The Mellow Drive as well as flight scope technology and new golf balls will all form part of the day. The event will boast a relaxing lounge where players can interact around the flight-tracker television and see their scores, brag about those amazing shots and joke about those hooks and slices. For only R50 you can replay your shots. There is no limit to entries. Join in the best chip, greatest putt or the famous marshmallow drive. These activities will be free and aimed at getting the whole family involved.  Categories are for men, women, silver foxes (over 60), kiddies (six to 16 years) and development kiddies (also six to 16 years). Players will enjoy a great venue with our partners exhibiting their products. A variety of expo spots will be available at the tee-off area. Display places around the venue will give great exposure to car dealers and businesses alike. Tickets are available on Webtickets, snapscan and at Lowveld Media’s office. To partner with Lowvelder in the Longest Golf Drive Challenge contact 084 785 3598 or email localevents@caxton.co.za. 